history.text: Hi have you seen The Great Gatsby?
Yes, I think it deserves a higher rating than the critics have given it.
I was surprised that it only has an average rating, it's a good movie!
What is your favorite role in the film?
Jay, played by Leonardo Dicaprio as he is my favorite actor
Leonardo Dicaprio is great in about everything he does. I thought Toby Maguire did a good job as well. He's come a long way since his sitcom days
I agree
Do you usually like romantic dramas?
I do! The cast in this was truly amazing as well

Baz Luhrmann is a great director also
. He makes visually stunning movies
The critic reviews are so negative, I don't understand why

I enjoy the way the story is told with the Nick Carraway character recalling his time with Gatsby
. It's very engaging storytelling
Viewers seem to agree as the Rotten Tomatoes rating is also average
The party scenes in particular are over the top, and fun. A real interesting peak into the time period. Any scenes you remember jumping out?
None that I can remember, it was awhile back that I saw it. I do know that Joel Edgerton didn't stand out to me as the best role in the movie, unlike the opinions of the critics

I can't believe the film had a $190 million budget. It's so expensive to make fil
ms nowadays
I do remember the scene where Daisy says she loves Gatsby but can't bring herself to say she doesn't love Tom
The scene where Gatsby hits and kills Myrtle with his car was shocking, and unexpected
Well, Gatsby car hit her that is
That was so shocking.  Also when Gatsby admitted he was born penniless
Did you prefer to see Daisy end up with Gatsby or Tom?
I agree, the scene where the truth about Gatsby's past comes out was really interesting.
I can't believe it's been 5 years since this movie came out

Personally, I was wanting Daisy to end up with Gatsby since he is such an interes
ting character
Yes me too. The movie is named after him,  after all.
The tragic ending where Myrtle's husband George shoots Gatsby , and then himself was a classic ending
That was such a twist! I never saw it coming did you?
They teased it a bit when George assumed Gatsby was having an affair with his wife. I knew something bad was going to happen
Yes there was some foreshadowing but I was hoping it wasn't going that route.  Such a great movie
I enjoyed how they tied it all together at the end of the film with the title of the memoir being The Great Gatsby. Overall and enjoyable classic film
